<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A good starting point for thinking about Elon =
Musk=E2=80=99s decision to buy Twitter Inc., back in April, is that it did =
not involve any spreadsheets. Like, when Musk decided to offer $54.20 per s=
hare to buy Twitter, that was not based on any detailed financial modeling;=
 Musk=E2=80=99s offers to buy companies are generally pretty whimsical, and=
 420 is a weed joke. Eventually, as the deal started to go bad, <a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29250431.285527/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDctMDkvZWxvbi1zLW91dD9j=
bXBpZD1CQkQxMDAzMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV=
3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjEwMDMmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cB5bd9aaf7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" tar=
get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Musk demanded</a> that Twitter send him=
=C2=A0<em>its=C2=A0</em>bankers=E2=80=99 working financial model, which is =
pretty unusual in big public mergers and acquisitions,=C2=A0and suggests th=
at Musk might not have had a working model of his own.<a class=3D"footnote-=
index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; di=
splay: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Why would he?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Similarly, after Musk announced that he wanted=
 to buy Twitter, he went looking for financing, including equity financing:=
 He wanted other people to invest in the deal alongside him. Last week, <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29250431.285527/aHR0c=
HM6Ly9zMy5kb2N1bWVudGNsb3VkLm9yZy9kb2N1bWVudHMvMjMxMDgzNTcvcmVkYWN0ZWQtdmVy=
c2lvbi1vZi1leGhpYml0cy1hLWotdG8tbGV0dGVyLXRvLXRoZS1ob25vcmFibGUta2F0aGFsZWV=
uLXN0LWotbWNjb3JtaWNrLWZyb20tZWR3YXJkLWIucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1627=
5a47" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;"> an assortment of text messages</a> from Musk=E2=80=99s phone=
 became public as part of the preparation for the trial, later this month, =
about whether Musk can get out of the deal he signed in April. Some of thes=
e texts are Musk=E2=80=99s friends, acquaintances and strangers texting him=
 to say =E2=80=9Chey can I invest with you=E2=80=9D and Musk saying =E2=80=
=9CI would love that=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Csure whatever=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=
=9Cno, not you,=E2=80=9D as the case may be. The general approach is refres=
hingly casual. Here are=C2=A0Musk and Larry Ellison on April 20 (the day th=
at Musk delivered <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
29250431.285527/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTg=
wOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDQ4MTI4L3RtMjIxMzIyOWQxX3NjMTNkYS5odG0/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB1491df2f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> his financing commitments</a> to Twitter):</=
p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk: </strong>Roughly what dollar siz=
e? Not holding you to anything, but the deal is oversubscribed,=C2=A0so I h=
ave to reduce or kick out some participants.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Ellison:</strong> A billion =E2=80=A6=
=C2=A0or whatever you recommend</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> Whatever works for you.=
 I=E2=80=99d recommend maybe $2B or more. This has very high potential and =
I=E2=80=99d rather have you than anyone else.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Ellison:</strong> I agree that it has =
huge potential =E2=80=A6=C2=A0and it would be lots of fun.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> Absolutely :)</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ellison <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/29250431.285527/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9l=
ZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDU2MDU1L3RtMjIxNDYwOC0xX3NjMTNkYS5=
odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdb340ff7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> came in for $1 billion</a>=
. =E2=80=9CThe deal is oversubscribed=E2=80=9D is just sort of a figure of =
speech.=C2=A0Obviously the deal was not oversubscribed, and in fact a month=
 later Musk was still openly <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/29250431.285527/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9k=
YXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDY0NjU1L3RtMjIxNjkzMWQxX3NjMTNkYS5odG0/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB213c38de" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> hunting for more equity investors<=
/a>. But it would be weird <em>not=C2=A0</em>to say =E2=80=9Cthe deal is ov=
ersubscribed=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0it would sound desperate=C2=A0=E2=80=
=94=C2=A0so Musk did.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or here is Michael Grimes, Musk=E2=80=99s lead=
 banker at Morgan Stanley, pitching him on crypto mogul Sam Bankman-Fried o=
n April 25 (the day he <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/29250431.285527/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLz=
E0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTE3NzIwL2QzMTkxOTBkZXg5OTEuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cBeb71618f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">signed the deal to buy Twitter</a>):</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Grimes:</strong> Sam Bankman-Fried is =
why I=E2=80=99m calling. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> ???</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> I=E2=80=99m backlogged =
with a mountain of critical work matters. Is this urgent?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Grimes:</strong> Wants 1-5b. Serious a=
bout partner w/you. Same security you own. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Grimes:</strong> Could do 5bn if every=
thing vision lock. Would do the engineering for social media blockchain int=
egration. Founded FTX crypto exchange. Believes in your mission. Major Demo=
cratic donor. So thought it was potentially worth an hour tomorrow a la the=
 Orlando meeting and he said he could shake hands on 5 if you like him and =
I think you will. Can talk when you have more time not urgent but if tomorr=
ow works out it could get us 5bn equity in an hour.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk replied by <em>hitting the =E2=80=9Cdisli=
ke=E2=80=9D tapback button</em>. (To be fair, he also replied that =E2=80=
=9CBlockchain twitter isn=E2=80=99t possible,=E2=80=9D agreed to meet =E2=
=80=9Cso long as I don=E2=80=99t have to have a laborious blockchain debate=
,=E2=80=9D and asked if Bankman-Fried actually had $3 billion liquid. Ultim=
ately Bankman-Fried and FTX never signed commitments to invest in Twitter, =
though Binance, another crypto exchange, was in for $500 million.) The poin=
t I want to make here is that Elon Musk has attained=C2=A0a level of wealth=
 and power where sometimes he gets text messages offering him $5 billion an=
d he=C2=A0<em>replies with a thumbs-down and moves on with his day</em>.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">People got mad about these texts? <a href=3D"h=
